'''[[absolute]] [[superlative]]''' (''plural'' '''absolute superlatives''')

#In Italian, Spanish, and Catalan; the form of an [[adjective]] formed by adding the suffix ''[[-issimo]]'', ''[[-isimo]]'', or ''[[-íssim]]'' respectively to the adjective (with any final vowel dropped) to express a [[superlative]] that cannot be exceeded, having the sense "as ... as possible".
